### 1. Actuators & Motion ($3,000–3,500)
- **Motors**: MyActuator RMD-X8 Pro BLDC ($250 × 12 = $3,000)
- **Transmission**: 3D-printed cycloidal drives (<$50/joint)
- **Encoders**: AS5600 magnetic sensors ($5 each)
- **Reasoning**: High torque density + low cost + ROS2 compatibility


### 2. Sensors & Perception ($1,200–1,500)
- Intel RealSense D435i (RGB-D + IMU, $300)
- Logitech C920 webcams ×2 ($100 each)
- ReSpeaker 4-Mic Array ($80)
- BNO055 IMU ($50)
- Foot load cells ($100)


### 3. Compute ($1,200–1,500)
- NVIDIA Jetson Orin NX (16GB, $1,000)
- Teensy 4.1 MCUs ×4 ($30 each)
- CAN bus backbone + USB for sensors


### 4. Power ($1,000–1,200)
- 12S4P Li-ion 21700 pack (~1kWh, $600)
- Daly Smart BMS ($100)
- Pre-charge + relay circuits ($100)
- Hot-swap connectors ($50)


### 5. Structure ($2,000–2,500)
- Aluminum extrusion 2020 profiles ($300)
- CNC brackets + 3D-printed shells ($1,000)
- ABS torso panels ($200)
- Feet with retractable omni-wheels ($500)


### 6. Hands & Manipulation ($600–800)
- OpenHand Model T (~$400)
- Tendon-driven servos + tactile sensors ($200)


**Total: $9,000 ± $1,000**
